# Decisions

## 2026-07-03 — Main screen architecture

### General idea

MyBudget is a simple budget tracker for beginners.

The main screen answers one question:

**How is my money situation for the selected period?**

---

### Period switcher

The app uses one main period switcher:

- Week
- Month
- Year
- All time

The selected period controls:

- the text in the top card;
- the date range;
- income amount;
- expense amount;
- period balance;
- transaction list;
- Money Mood color.

---

### Top card

The top card shows:

- selected period name;
- remaining amount for this period;
- date range;
- Money Mood visual state.

Example:

```text
Остаток за неделю
3 500 ₽
8 мая — 14 мая 2026


Only the top card changes color according to Money Mood.

The full screen background does not change color.

Income and expense cards

The income and expense cards have two roles:

Show total income and expense for the selected period.
Work as buttons for adding a new transaction.

Income card opens the income form.

Expense card opens the expense form.

Transaction list

The list shows only transactions from the selected period.

Transactions are grouped by date.

Income is green.

Expense is red.

Bottom navigation

MVP navigation:

Main
Savings
Statistics
Settings
```

## 2026-07-03 — Balance adjustment

The balance card can be manually adjusted.

If the user edits the displayed balance, the application calculates the difference between the current balance and the entered balance.

The difference is automatically saved as a transaction.

Examples:

Current balance: 3500
New balance: 3200

↓

Expense 300
Note: "Adjustment"

---

Current balance: 3500
New balance: 3800

↓

Income 300
Note: "Adjustment"

The user never edits the database balance directly.

The balance is always changed through automatically created transactions.

Adjustment transactions are shown in the transaction history like normal transactions.

They are not hidden.

Reason:

The user must clearly see why the balance changed.

Adjustments are part of the financial history.

---

# Transactions

Path:

```text
users/{userId}/transactions/{transactionId}
Purpose

Transactions store all income and expense records of one user.

Each user has their own transactions collection.
```

### Transaction editing

Transactions must have visually available editing.

Long press is not used because the app is a website and must work clearly on mobile and desktop.

Each transaction item shows an edit button.

Clicking the edit button opens the transaction edit form.

If the note is empty, the interface displays the transaction type:

- Income
- Expense

The database can store an empty note.

## note: ""

## Transaction form

Income and expense use the same form.

The form works in two modes:

- income
- expense

The user opens income form by clicking the income card.

The user opens expense form by clicking the expense card.

Required field:

- amount

Optional field:

- note

Automatic field:

- transaction date and time

The transaction date and time are set to the current moment by default.

The user can manually edit date and time.

The user does not manually select transaction type inside the form.

The type is defined by the button that opened the form.

# MyBudget

## Mission

Make personal finance tracking so simple that adding a transaction takes only a few seconds.

The application should never force the user to enter information that is not necessary at that moment.

Simple actions must always remain simple.

## Transaction screen

Transaction creation uses a dedicated screen.

The main screen never contains transaction input fields.

The transaction screen has two modes:

- Add Income
- Add Expense

The layout is identical.

Only the title, accent color and transaction type change.

After saving, the user automatically returns to the main screen.

### MVP Rule

A feature is included in the first version only if it helps the user complete the main task.

Future functionality may be prepared in the architecture, but it should not appear in the interface until it becomes useful.

## Initial currency selection

The application does not ask for currency during registration.

Currency is requested only before the first financial transaction.

A transaction can be:

- Income
- Expense
- Balance adjustment

After the user selects a currency, it is stored in user settings and automatically applied to all new transactions.

The currency can be changed later in Settings.

Previous transactions keep their original currency.

## Transaction deletion

When the user deletes a transaction, the app shows a temporary message:

"Операция удалена"

The message includes an Undo button:

"Отменить"

The Undo action is available for 5 seconds.

If the user clicks Undo, the transaction is restored.

If the user does not click Undo within 5 seconds, the deletion becomes final.

MVP does not include a trash bin.

## Transaction editing

The same transaction screen is used for creating and editing transactions.

Modes:

- create-income
- create-expense
- edit

In edit mode, the user can change:

- amount
- note
- transaction date
- transaction time

Changing transaction type is not included in MVP.

If the user created the wrong transaction type, they can delete it and create a new one.

## Smart notes MVP

The app saves transaction notes automatically.

When the user starts typing in the note field, the app shows matching saved notes.

Example:

User types: "Б"

Suggestion: "Бензин"

MVP does not show separate sections for recent or popular notes.

The architecture stores usageCount and lastUsedAt for future improvements.

## Current Balance

The current balance is independent of the selected period.

It always represents the user's actual available money.

Only income, expense, transaction history and financial mood depend on the selected period.

## Balance and period logic

The top balance card shows the current balance.

Current balance is calculated from all transactions and does not depend on the selected period.

The period selector affects only:

- income amount;
- expense amount;
- transaction list;
- period analytics;
- Money Mood.

Period balance is not the same as current balance.

Current balance answers:

"How much money do I have now?"

Period analytics answers:

"What happened during this period?"

## Money values

Every money value consists of two independent parts:

- amount — numeric value;
- currency — ISO 4217 currency code.

Example:

15000 KGS

The app does not use currency names that require grammatical declension, such as "сом", "сома", "сомов".

This keeps the interface simple and prepares the app for multiple currencies.
